And then comes this amazing two paragraphs where you get the essence of what it would be like to be at sea all the time.

392
00:39:14,320 --> 00:39:35,360
Know ye now, Baltington, glimpses do you seem to see of that mortally intolerable truth that all deep earnest thinking is but the intrepid effort of the soul to keep the open independence of her sea, while the wildest winds of heaven and earth conspire to cast her on the treacherous slavish shore.

393
00:39:35,679 --> 00:39:45,039
Now, now, this comes this praise of Baltington, but in landlessness alone resides the highest truth, shoreless, indefinite as God.

394
00:39:45,039 --> 00:39:51,840
So better it is to perish in the howling infinite than being gloriously dashed upon the leaf, even if it were safe.

395
00:39:51,840 --> 00:39:56,800
Take heart, take heart, O Baltington, bear thee grimly, demigod.

396
00:39:56,800 --> 00:40:03,120
Up from the spray of thy ocean perishing, leaps straight up thy apotheosis.

397
00:40:03,119 --> 00:40:04,000
One or two.

