00:43:04,320 --> 00:43:08,079
And I think that's a great move on Melville's part.

432
00:43:09,920 --> 00:43:16,559
So the Oberman is grim and perishes in the Holy Infinite, and that's that.

433
00:43:16,880 --> 00:43:21,519
That is, there is this extreme possibility of the absence of all meaning.

434
00:43:21,920 --> 00:43:24,559
Don't even trust any divine glimmers.

435
00:43:24,559 --> 00:43:28,880
Take no comfort from any interpretation.

436
00:43:28,880 --> 00:43:32,640
Confront the indefinite head-on.

437
00:43:32,639 --> 00:43:43,400
